cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.PF 

The paper discusses the scalability and stability of cellular networks in the context of IoT, which involves wireless communication and network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also utilizes mathematical modeling and queueing theory, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The analysis and comparison of different transmission strategies involve control and optimization, which could relate to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.PF (Performance).
